						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarājadēva. Year 3+1: A.D. 1127.</hi></p>						

						<p>Gift of one <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> for two evening lamps <hi rend="italic">(chandyā dīpam)</hi> to be lighted perpetually in the temple of Teṉṉūrpadi by Cheṭṭi, the wife of Mūkkaṉ, a merchant of Maṉaiyāmpaḍi in Vāyaṟaikkāl-nāḍu. The two <hi rend="italic">śivabrāhmaṇas</hi> who had the <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> right in the temple undertook to maintain the lamp.</p>						

						</summary>
